<HEADLINE> German Wins One-meter Title at Euro Diving Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Andreas Wels claimed
the first title at the European swimming championships when he won
the men's one-meter springboard diving event in Seville, Spain, on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Wels' teammate Holger Schlepps overtook Spaniard Rafael Alvarez
to clinch the silver medal with a near-perfect final dive.
</P>
<P>
Wels collected 362.10 points from his six dives, beating
Schlepps by 5.02 points. Alvarez finished third in 355.56 points.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
