<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Foreign Affairs And Trade Official Visits China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- William Farmer, the deputy
secretary of Australia's Foreign Affairs and Trade Department, and
his Chinese hosts today held consultations on bilateral relations
and other issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
The two sides reached agreement on many issued, according to a
Chinese source.
</P>
<P>
Both sides agreed that China and Australia have enjoyed sound
relations and have many prospects for development. Any
confrontations involving human rights will be detrimental to the
improvement and protection of human rights, they said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides stood for continued dialogues and co-operation
for human rights, and said that both China and Australia are
willing to make an effort to further improve bilateral relations
and co-operation in international affairs.
</P>
<P>
Farmer and his party are here on a four-day visit as guests
of Li Zhaoxing, Chinese Vice-foreign Minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
