<HEADLINE> Israeli Opposition Labor Leader to Visit France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The chief of Israel's opposition
Labor Party, Ehud Barak, will pay a five-day "half-private" visit
to France from Sunday, said the Israeli embassy here today.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Barak will meet with Prime Minister Lionel
Jospin, Foreign Minister Hubert Vedrine and Minister of Finance
and Economy Dominique Strauss-Kahn.
</P>
<P>
He could also be received by President Jacques Chirac, said the
embassy.
</P>
<P>
No details about the content of his talks with French leaders
were given, but they are expected to be focused on the situation
of the Middle East peace process and the situation in southern
Lebanon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
