<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pak PM Greets Indian Counterpart on Independence Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif greeted his Indian counterpart Inder Kumar Gujral on the
occasion of India's Independence Day which falls on August 15, the
official Associated Press of Pakistan reported this evening.
</P>
<P>
"Excellency, on behalf of the people and the government of
Pakistan and on my own behalf, I wish to convey warmest
felicitations to the government and the people of India on the
occasion of the independence day of the Republic of India," Sharif
said in his message.
</P>
<P>
"This year, the independence day of both our countries has an
added significance," said Shairf. "It marks 50 years of our
existence as independent and sovereign nations."
</P>
<P>
"On this historic occasion let us resolve to bequeath to the
succeeding generations in India and Pakistan peace and
prosperity," Sharif said.
</P>
<P>
"I reiterate that we in Pakistan remain committed to the
improvement of relations with India and to address all outstanding
issues through a meaningful and comprehensive dialogue so that we
may be able to focus our energies on economic development and the
well-being of our peoples," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
