<HEADLINE> Former Zambian President Denies Arson Accusation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Former Zambian President Kenneth
Kaunda today denied that his United National Independence Party
(UNIP) is responsible for the burning of the old Soweto market on
Tuesday evening.
</P>
<P>
UNIP is not as heartless and devilish as to gain political
mileage through people's misery, he said.
</P>
<P>
He accused the government of looking for an excuse by
declaring a state of emergency in order to distabilize UNIP and
later ban it.
</P>
<P>
The government said on Tuesday that UNIP was responsible for
the disturbances.
</P>
<P>
The burning of the stalls triggered off riots on Wednesday in
the capital city. More than 60 people were arrested and dozens
of others injured in the clashes between policemen and vendors,
who went on rampage in protest against the arson. 
