<HEADLINE> Zambian Leader Calls for Investment in Human </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Zambian Vice President Godfrey
Miyanda today called for investment in human development to
realize the country's goals in science and technology.
</P>
<P>
He said in a written speech read by Deputy Minister of
Education Betram Meembe, Zambia needs people of academic
excellence, creative minds and practical skills to spearhead
necessary development in the country.
</P>
<P>
Zambia recognizes that there can be no competitiveness in its
goods and services without an advancement in science and
technology, Miyanda noted.
</P>
<P>
The vice president called for public support so that all
Zambians possess some basic knowledge of science and technology
to help the country flourish.
</P>
<P>
"Our own perception of national needs have swung firmly
towards planners, economists, doctors, builders and scientists
of high calibre," he said. 
</P>
