<HEADLINE> EC to Transfer Uganda 50 Million Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Uganda and the European
Commission (EC) have signed a Stabilisation Export (STABEX)
agreement under which the latter, under the Lome Four Convention
will transfer to the former 50 million U.S. dollars to make up
for its loss of earnings in coffee and hides for the years 1993
and 1995.
</P>
<P>
The signing ceremony took place here today.
</P>
<P>
E. Gunnar Ring, the charge d'affairs of the European Union in
Uganda and the Ugandan minister of state for finance Mathew
Rukikaire signed the agreement on behalf of their respective
institution and government.
</P>
<P>
Ring revealed that Ugandan government through the Lome
Convention has qualified for the transfer for the years 1993 and
1995 which totals up to 56 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Rukikaire hailed the European Commission for providing the
funds which he said will be used to upgrade and rehabilitate the
trunk roads in the country, support universal primary education
and general policies in agriculture and agri-processing. 
</P>
