<HEADLINE> S. Leone Accused of Attacking ECOMOG Forces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria today accused Sierra
Leone's military junta of attacking positions of the west African
peacekeeping force, known as ECOMOG, in the country.
</P>
<P>
A statement from the defense headquarters said the attacks
"are contrary to the ceasefire agreement and the impressions
created by some respected Sierra Leoneans on the need for
continued talks with ECOWAS (Economic Community of West African
States)".
</P>
<P>
It noted that the coupists have breached the ceasefire
agreement, reached last month in Cote d'Ivoire, by their new
offensives not only on ECOMOG positions but also on innocent
citizens in Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
Under such circumstances, the ECOMOG troops would continue to
defend themselves and take other necessary actions as directed by
ECOWAS.
</P>
<P>
The statement followed the accusation by the junta of being
attacked by ECOMOG soldiers around Lungi international airport
near the capital Freetown.
</P>
<P>
A defense source of Sierra Leone's military government said
earlier today that some units of the ECOMOG contingent based in
the airport had moved from their positions and tried to use the
cover of darkness to attack government positions around the
airport area Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Casualty figures have not been released, however the source
said the government soldiers did not suffer any loss in the
fighting launched by ECOMOG with the help of such heavy weapons
as artillery.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of local residents fled in all directions during the
long fighting, while a number of houses were destroyed, he said,
adding that ECOMOG should be blamed for most of the destruction.
</P>
<P>
A number of clashes have taken place between the two sides
since the coupists toppled Sierra Leone's elected government led
by ousted President Ahmed Tejan Kabbah on May 25.
</P>
<P>
ECOWAS has announced full-scale economic sanctions against the
junta after it announced it would stay in power for four years.
The sub-regional body has also threatened to use force to flush
out the junta. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
