<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Korean President Stresses Peaceful Reunification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, August 15 (Xinhua) -- South Korean President Kim
Young-sam said today that regardless of circumstance, the
reunification of the Korean peninsula should be achieved peacefully.
</P>
<P>
The time had come when South Korea and the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK) should clearly perceive the true meaning
of peace and work to achieve it, Kim said. His speech marked the
52nd anniversary of the Korean Peninsula's independence after 36
years of Japanese colonial rule.
</P>
<P>
"Peace, above all, means the renunciation of arms," Kim said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the four-party talks -- comprising South Korea,
the DPRK, along with China and the United States -- should be a
forum for dialogue based on mutual confidence.
</P>
<P>
The four parties held talks in New York last week to arrange
formal negotiations aimed at forging a permanent peace mechanism
on the Korean Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
Senior leaders from the four parties failed to set an agenda
for the formal peace talks but agreed to try again on September 15
in New York. 
</P>
</TEXT>
