<HEADLINE> HK Police Launch Anti-Triad Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong police launched an
anti-triad operation today and smashed a triad gang active in Wan
Chai and Central, a police spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
After six months' covert investigations, officers from the
Organized Crime and Triad Bureau mounted the operation in the
early hours of today in which more than 30 locations were raided.
</P>
<P>
As a result, 25 men and eight women aged between 15 and 52 were
arrested for a wide range of triad-related offenses, including
managing a triad society, claiming to be member of a triad
society, recruiting triad members, wounding, extortion and
trafficking in dangerous drugs.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, six beef knives, two machetes, a
number of ski-masks and gloves, as well as a small quantity of
suspected marijuana and cocaine were seized.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that the operation to trace other target
suspects is still underway. 
</P>
