<HEADLINE> Trade Fair In Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The '97 Kunming Export Trade
Fair ended today in China's Yunnan Province with 1.57 billion US
dollars worth in business volume.
</P>
<P>
The business volume represents an increase of 24.5 percent over
that of the previous fair which was attended by more than 8,700
business people from 56 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Export trade was worth 417 million US dollars, with industrial
products accounting for 70 percent. Exports of agricultural
products, which accounted for the majority of business in the
past, made up only 15.4 percent this time.
</P>
<P>
This indicates that southwestern parts of China have made major
progress in industrial production, an official related to the fair
said.
</P>
<P>
Co-operation with Southeast Asian countries has grown and
exports to Myanmar, Thailand, Vietnam, and Indonesia have grown to
79.3 million US dollars and business volume for border trade
reached 75.5 million US dollars, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Kunming Export Trade Fair was jointly sponsored by Yunnan,
Sichuan and Guizhou provinces, the Tibet and Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous regions, and Chongqing municipality. 
</P>
</TEXT>
