<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-15 15:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Technician Arrested After Cairo's Shop Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The maintenance technician at a
Cairo shopping mall was arrested today in connection with the
deadly fire in the mall on Thursday midnight, the Egyptian MENA
news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The man, whose name was not given, will be remanded in custody
for four days pending investigation under an order issued at noon
today by the East Cairo District Attorney Counselor Hisham Hmouda,
according to the MENA report.
</P>
<P>
Three were killed and more than 280 injured in the fire that
raged through the crowded shopping center for two hours on the eve
of the Muslim prayer holiday. Criminal lab experts started
investigations into the reasons behind the fire.
</P>
<P>
Several technicians at the mall attributed the fire to a short
circuit, saying electric cables were overloaded. Shop owners at
the mall were notified more than once about the dangerous
situation there, they added.
</P>
<P>
The fire gutted the fifth and sixth stories of the mall besides
 its movie house. Several shops at the third and fourth floors
were also severely damaged.
</P>
<P>
The first of fire engines arrived 30 minutes after the fire
broke out because of the difficulty to drive through the
overcrowded streets all around the mall.
</P>
<P>
When the fire broke out, the seven-story Al-Horreya Mall in the
Cairo suburb of Helioplis was full of late-night shoppers and
merry-makers who came to enjoy a cool summer time.
</P>
<P>
The report said 252 injured, most of them suffering from
suffocation due to inhaling smoke caused by the fire, remain in
hospital.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary investigations showed that the building lacks all
emergency preparations including emergency stairs and has no
emergency ventilation systems or exits.
</P>
<P>
Those who happened to be at the building during the fire had
to smash the building's windows to allow fresh air in, especially
after its central air conditioning stopped functioning. Panicked,
some jumped out of the windows for life.
</P>
<P>
Reports on the cause and the site of the fire are varied and
contradictory.
</P>
<P>
Some say the fire started in either the second or fourth floor
while some survivors said that it erupted in the sixth
floor. Other survivors said that the fire ensued from a short
circuit at an elevator under repair at the mall.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitnesses heard a deafening sound of a crack before the
outbreak of the fire and agreed that the power failure left the
entire building in darkness.
</P>
<P>
At hand at the scene to supervise fire-fighting operations were
Minister of Health and Population Ismail Sallam and governor of
Cairo Abdel Rehim Shehata. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
