<HEADLINE> Olympic Champ Deng Sails into Third Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- China's four-time Olympic
champion Deng Yaping cruised into the women's singles third round
at the Australian table tennis tournament in Melbourne Friday
evening.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old Deng, the best women player of the modern era,
crushed Japanese Yuki Takakusa 21-15, 21-13, 21-8 with lightning
fast attacks.
</P>
<P>
Seventh seed Chan Tan Lui, from Hong Kong, China, went down
21-12, 18-21, 21-18, 21-17 to Chinese Fan Jianxin who plays for a
Japanese club.
</P>
<P>
No.13 seed Keiko Okazaki of Japan was the other seeded
casualty. She lost to South Korean Han Kwang Sun 21-14, 24-22,
21-23, 22-20.
</P>
<P>
Australian first round winners, Miao Miao, Yvonne Li, Tammy
Gough, Sarah Doolan, Kay Crowell and Jian Fang Lay, were all
eliminated in the second round.
</P>
<P>
Chinese stars Yang Ying and Wang Chen beat Lay and Gough
respectively.
</P>
<P>
In the men's second round, Chinese Ding Song rolled over
Australian Jeff Plumb 21-15, 21-11, 21-14 and his teammate Yan
Sen, singles bronze medalist in the world championships in May
this year, easily beat Chinese Taipei's Chin Chin Long.
</P>
<P>
Chinese youngster Ma Lin, who finished second to teammate and
former world champion Kong Linghui in the U.S. Open last month,
routed Australian Simon Gerada to reach the third round. 
</P>
