<HEADLINE> Indonesian Rupiah Plunges 200 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's rupiah plummeted
again today, the second day following the government's decision to
float the currency.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah tumbled to a record low of 2,840 to the U.S. dollar
this afternoon, reducing 200 points from Wednesday, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, State Minister for National Development Planning
Ginandjar Kartasasmita said here today that the government
decision has long been considered, especially after neighboring
countries did the same.
</P>
<P>
Bank Indonesia (the central bank) Governor Soedradjad
Djiwandono announced Thursday that as of that day, the Monetary
Authorities have decided to float the exchange value of the rupiah
by abandoning a set trading band.
</P>
<P>
On the rupiah fluctuations, Ginandjar said they pose no problem
because the country's economic foundation is strong with foreign
exchange reserves reaching 21 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
To defend the rupiah fluctuation which began in the middle of
July, the central bank had widened the spread of rupiah exchange
band from 8 percent to 12 percent. The government had also sold
1.5 billion U.S. dollars as well as raised overnight interest
rate.
</P>
<P>
But the measures had no obvious effects as "the regional
factor" was the main factor affecting the value of the rupiah,
official sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
