<DOCNO> XIE19970815.0065 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Co-operating With the New Hong Kong Government: Commissioner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- There is no relationship of
subordination between the Office of the Commissioner of the
Ministry of Foreign Affairs in Hong Kong and the Government of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR), a Chinese
diplomat says.
</P>
<P>
According to Ma Yuzhen, the first commissioner of the Chinese
Foreign Ministry in Hong Kong, the two will work for the common
goal of maintaining state sovereignty and promoting the long-term
prosperity and stability of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Ma's comments come in Beijing's "Outlook" magazine for Monday
where he says they co-operate and have a division of labor in a
relationship of "mutual support, mutual respect, mutual trust, and
close cooperation."
</P>
<P>
To do a good job in diplomatic and foreign affairs for Hong
Kong, the commissioner's office will have more contacts and will
consult the HKSAR government and not intervene in the autonomy of
the HKSAR, he said, noting that his office will adopt a pioneering
and cautious attitude and solve new problems with a new way of
thinking.
</P>
<P>
The function of the Chinese Foreign Ministry commissioner's
office in Hong Kong, Ma said, is different from that of Chinese
embassies in other countries in that it is a functional organ of
the Central Government in the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
"We work on the territory of our own country and are concerned
only with diplomatic matters concerning Hong Kong. We have no
diplomatic privileges or immunity," he explained.
</P>
<P>
Ma said he made the acquaintance of Tung Chee-Hwa, the chief
executive of the HKSAR, while serving as ambassador to Britain and
built a good relationship with him.
</P>
<P>
Over the past month or more, Ma said, he has developed close
co-operation with Tung Chee-Hwa, and other members of the office
have had contacts with HKSAR departments. He believes that his
office will have even closer co-operation with the HKSAR in
future.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
