<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Cabinet Reshuffled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government announced
today a cabinet reshuffle, which has been approved by King
Bhumibol Adulyadej.
</P>
<P>
Two newcomers, former deputy prime minister Thaksin Shinawatra
and former finance minister Virabhongse Ramangura, both non-MPs,
joined the cabinet as deputy prime ministers.
</P>
<P>
Thaksin is a telecom tycoon, while Virabhongse is an economist
who negotiated with the International Monetary Fund during the
Prem Tinsulanonda government.
</P>
<P>
Virabhongse will oversee economic affairs while Thaksin's role
is not yet known.
</P>
<P>
The Education Ministry underwent the most thorough shakeup with
its minister Sukavich Rangsipol and all three deputy ministers
removed. But Sukavich retained his deputy premiership.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister's Office Minister Chingchai Mongkoltham has been
made the education minister.
</P>
<P>
Minister of University Affairs Montri Danpaibul and Minister of
Labor and Social Welfare Chatchai Ieasakul swapped their posts.
</P>
<P>
Other removals and appointments involved six deputy ministers.
</P>
<P>
The reshuffle is aimed at improving the government's image and
ability in reviving the country's economy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
