<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Continuing Narcotics Control Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- According to a decision made
during a committee meeting today on anti-drug work, China's
National Narcotics Control Committee will extend its nationwide
anti-drug operation to the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
From April, when China started the operation, to June, public
security departments across the country established 187 new drug
rehabilitation centers, sent 30,000 people to the centers, and
worked on 39,105 drug cases.
</P>
<P>
Public security departments arrested 55,211 people in drug
cases, seized 1,623 kg of heroin, 400 kg of the drug "ice", and
more than 100 tons of chemicals used for making drugs. During that
period, 499 drug networks and 1,196 places for dealing in drugs
were destroyed.
</P>
<P>
In south China's Guangdong province, 1,846 drug sales were
discovered and 3,801 people involved were arrested. Authorities
there discovered 33,648 drug addicts and sent 28,287 of them to
rehabilitation centers.
</P>
<P>
The crackdown has helped reduce the number of drug-related
cases. In the first half of the year, robberies and thefts were
down 27.9 percent and 22.8 percent respectively from the same 1995
period.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
