<HEADLINE> Myanmar, Thailand Open Border Friendship Bridge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar and Thailand today
officially inaugurated a friendship bridge on the Moei (Thaungyin)
River linking Myanmar's Myawaddy and Thailand's Maesot.
</P>
<P>
The opening of the bridge, which was jointly built by Myanmar
and Thailand, is expected to facilitate trade, transport and
communications between the two countries, adding a link in the
Asian highway construction plan project.
</P>
<P>
During Thai Prime Minister Chavalit Yongchaiyudh's last visit
to Myanmar in May, the two countries signed an agreement on border
crossing and exchanged notes concerning the jurisdiction over the
Thai-Myanmar Friendship Bridge.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar and Thailand began formal border trade activities in
March 1996 following the signing of a border trade agreement.
</P>
</TEXT>
