<HEADLINE> Hashimoto Expresses Condolences Over Sun's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro
Hashimoto expressed his condolences today over the death of Sun
Pinghua, president of the China-Japan Friendship Association.
</P>
<P>
"Mr. Sun played an active role for quite some time. We had
associated with each other for nearly 30 years, I feel we have
lost a person very special to Japan," Hashimoto told reporters.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Yukihiko Ikeda, in a telegram sent to the
association, said: "I cannot help but feel deep sorrow. I
sincerely express my condolences and recall Mr. Sun's achievements
in efforts to establish friendship between China and Japan."
</P>
<P>
Koichi Kato, secretary general of Japan's ruling Liberal
Democratic Party, said he regretted the death of Sun, who
contributed greatly to bilateral relations between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Sun played a major role in overcoming turbulent times in the
two countries' relations, Kato said.
</P>
<P>
Sun died in Beijing this morning at the age of 79. 
</P>
