<HEADLINE> Sino-Japanese Aviation Agreement Signed in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, August 15 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-Japanese aviation
memorandum on new flight routes and expanding co-operation was
signed today after four days of negotiations in this northern
Chinese port city.
</P>
<P>
The number of cities in China and Japan open to the two
countries' airlines will increase from 14 to 26 by adding the
cities of Tianjin, Wuhan, Shenyang, Chongqing, Kunming, and Xiamen
in China and Niigata, Okayama, Tomiyama, and Fukushima in Japan.
</P>
<P>
Cities with originating flights will increase from 12 to 26,
and two airlines will join the existing four to provide a 50
percent increase in the flights between the countries.
</P>
<P>
The agreement will go into effect by the end of this month,
when it gets final government approval from both sides. 
</P>
</TEXT>
