<HEADLINE> Mongolia Studies Conference Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Seventh international
Conference on Studies of Mongolia ended here today.
</P>
<P>
Up to 260 foreign scholars from 26 countries, and more than 100
local scholars attended the four-day conference and contributed
about 300 academic papers on their research on Mongolian history,
language, culture, art, politics and economy.
</P>
<P>
The participants also held lively discussion on political and
economic developments in modern Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
Professor Bira, a famous Mongolian scholar and the secretary
general of the International Federation of Studies of Mongolia
(IFSM), told reporters that more and more foreign scholars were
involved in research on Mongolia in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Others were interested in the politics, economy and laws of
modern Mongolia, he added.
</P>
<P>
Professor Chinggeltei, honorary president of the Research
Institute attached to the Inner Mongolian University and
deputy chairman of the IFSM, said Chinese scholars were in the
lead in research and studies on Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
More than 30 Chinese scholars participated in the conference.
</P>
</TEXT>
