<HEADLINE> Daya Bay Nuclear Power Plant In Smooth Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The Daya Bay Nuclear Power
Plant, China's first nuclear power plant built with foreign
investment has been running smoothly during the first seven months.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Guangdong Nuclear Power Joint Venture
Co. Ltd announced at a press conference today that as of July 31,
the nuclear power plant had provided 6.44 billion kw/hours of
electricity for the power grid of Guangdong and Hong Kong, 612
million more than for the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
He said that the plant completed 53.68 percent of its annual
plan by the end of July and is expected to send 12 billion
kw/hours of electricity into the power grid by the end of December.
</P>
<P>
The plant began its third refueling and maintenance program for
two of its generating units at the beginning of the year, and the
two are now operating at full capacity.
</P>
<P>
The plant has had strict controls on radioactive waste.
Discharged waste gas only accounted for 1.65 percent of the
state's limited amount and waste water accounted for 1.38 percent
of the state level.
</P>
<P>
Measurements taken by seven radioactivity monitoring stations
in a 10-kilometer area around the station indicate that
radioactivity levels are at the same level as last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
