<HEADLINE> 4 Die in Sea Accident in Metro Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- A sightseeing boat carrying 49
people capsized at sunset time in Manila Bay, four were reportedly
killed and at least six were still missing.
</P>
<P>
Investigators said 45 tourists and four crew members were
aboard the ship when the mishap happened at 4:30 p.m. Among the
missing were two crew members and two Japanese tourists.
</P>
<P>
A rescue team from the Philippine Navy was searching for the
missing ones, but darkness hampered the effort.
</P>
<P>
A local TV report said there were 35 people missing, mostly
Hong Kong citizens.  
</P>
