<HEADLINE> Nanjing Expands Opening Drive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Nanjing, an ancient city in east
China's Jiangsu province, has made great headway in its opening
drive, with investments totaling 5.9 billion US dollars
4,653 foreign-funded enterprises established.
</P>
<P>
According to Vice-Mayor Huang Mengfu, Nanjing, an important
city in the Yangtze River economic belt, enjoys a favorable
geographical location, advanced science and technology, and
highly developed industrial and economic sectors.
</P>
<P>
A large number of transnational corporations and consortia have
poured investments into the city.
</P>
<P>
Nanjing has established extensive cooperative ties with over 60
countries and regions in the fields of construction,
telecommunications, electronics, chemicals, machine-building,
petroleum prospecting, maritime transportation and medical and
health services.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the city has established 67 enterprises in a
number of countries and regions, including the United States,
Germany, Russia, Yemen and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Nanjing has also established trade and economic relations with
119 countries and regions across the world. The city's total 1996
imports and exports of 4.03 billion US dollars ranked at the
forefront nationwide.
</P>
<P>
Huang noted that the city has invested more than 10 billion
yuan over the past few years to improve its investment environment
and has been appraised as one of the nation's top 40 cities in
that regard. 
</P>
