<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Surname Li Now World's No. One Family Name </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- People surnamed Li, known for
years as the Smiths of China, now belong to an elite group of
their own, having the most commonly-used family name in the world.
</P>
<P>
New statistics show that more than 87 million people, or 7.9
percent of China's majority of Han people, are surnamed Li. It
replaces Zhang, which is recorded in the Guinness Book of the
World Records, as the Number One Name in China.
</P>
<P>
But Li and Zhang are only two of over 10,000 family names used
by some 1.2 billion Chinese people of 56 ethnic groups, according
to the latest study of Yuan Yida and Du Ruofu with the Institute
of Genetics under the Chinese Academy of Sciences.
</P>
<P>
The surnames Li, Wang, Zhang, Liu and Chen are used by 350
million people, the researchers reported in their new book, "the
Great Dictionary of Chinese Family Names".
</P>
<P>
Zhao, Zhu and Kong, which were at the top of the surname lists
in different ancient books, rank 7th, 14th and 72nd in the new
book.
</P>
<P>
The dictionary includes 5,327 single-character family names,
4,329 with two characters and 2,316 names that have from three to
nine characters.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
