<HEADLINE> Jobless Rate Stands at 2.4 percent in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate in Hong
Kong stood at 2.4 percent in the three months ending in July,
while the underemployment rate dropped slightly to 1.2 percent,
according to the Census and Statistics Department today.
</P>
<P>
The jobless rate for the second season of 1997 was 2.4 percent,
while the underemployment rate, 1.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
A government spokesman said that the general situation on the
labor market has been stable over the past three months. Between
May and July this year, the unemployment rate declined in
construction, trade and transport sectors, but rose in
restaurants, hotels and business services sectors.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that overall demand for labor was firm on the
heel of further economic growth.  
</P>
