<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Releases Domestic Export Figures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's domestic exports
of machinery and textile products increased in the second quarter
of 1997, while those of electronic products and apparel decreased,
according to the Census and Statistics Department today.
</P>
<P>
Domestic exports classified to the four major industries --
textiles, apparel, machinery and electronics -- accounted for 69
percent of Hong Kong's total domestic exports of manufactured
goods.
</P>
<P>
Between April and June this year, domestic exports of machinery
rose by 11 percent to 10.1 billion HK dollars (1.3 billion US
dollars) compared with the same period of 1996, and domestic
exports of textile products went up by five percent to 10.2
billion HK dollars (1.31 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, domestic exports classified to the consumer electric
industries fell by eight percent to 5.9 billion HK dollars (760
million US dollars), and those to machinery industry decreased by
six percent to 8.8 billion HK dollars (1.1 billion US dollars).
</P>
