<HEADLINE> Georgia Agrees to End Abhkazia Conflict </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Georgia agreed today to end its
conflict with the breakaway republic of Abhkazia through peaceful
means, said an Itar-Tass news agency report from the Georgian
capital of Tibilisi.
</P>
<P>
Georgian President Eduard Shevardnadze and Vladislav Ardzinba,
leader of the Abkhazia republic of the country, signed a joint
statement in Tibilisi, pledging not to allow bloodshed again.
</P>
