<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Murder Cases Up Sharply in Singapore in 1st Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Reported cases of murder,
robbery and snatch theft registered increases in the first six
months of this year, while the total number of seizable offenses
dropped by five percent from last years' level.
</P>
<P>
In a report on the crime situation in the first half of this
year in Singapore today, police said that crime in Singapore
dipped slightly in the first half of the year.
</P>
<P>
The total number of seizable offenses fell by five percent, or
1,137 cases from the 23,936 cases in January-June 1996 to 22,799
cases in the same period this year.
</P>
<P>
It said that a significant decline was noted for housebreaking,
motor vehicle theft and cheating related offenses and outraging of
modesty.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, however, reported cases of murder, robbery
and snatch theft registered increases in the first half of this
year, it said.
</P>
<P>
The number of murder increased from 13 cases in the first six
months of 1996 to 30 over the same period this year, up by 130.8
percent, or almost reaching the whole-year level of 31 cases of
1996.
</P>
<P>
In three other cases, the victims were murdered while being
robbed. Nine murders involved victims who were foreigners, an
increase of three cases from the six cases a year ago, the police
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
