<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Higher On settled US Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Investors confidence that the
volatile United States market was settling down, was "the most
important" influence on the local sharemarket closing strongly
today.
</P>
<P>
"It was a very strong day and it was almost entirely due to
overseas," senior broker Bill Richmond said.
</P>
<P>
"The most important of all, the influences on Australian stocks
today was "the fact that the American market appears to be
settling down," he said.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index closed 38.8 points higher at 2,666.2,
with blue chip stocks leading the charge as well as better than
expected profit results this week from some major companies.
</P>
<P>
The all resources index was 23.3 points higher at 1,409.2 and
the all industrials index was 59.1 points higher at 4,280.1.
</P>
<P>
Diversified resources giant BHP gained 28 cents to 17.50
Australian dollars and mining giant Rio Tinto rose 43 cents to
21.48 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The gold index was 29.6 points higher at 1,337.7, with brokers
saying there was speculation of takeovers in the gold sector.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 320.82 million shares traded worth 673.34
million Australian dollars (498.27 million US dollars), and rises
of 657 outnumbered falls of 404.  
</P>
</TEXT>
