<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Marginally Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar finished
marginally lower today with its virtually flat closing levels
concealing a volatile day of trading.
</P>
<P>
It closed at 74.33 US cents down from 74.41 late Thursday. It
fell as low as 73.85 US cents in the morning and then rallied to a
high of 74.50 during the afternoon session.
</P>
<P>
Hopes of lower interest rates had undermined the local currency
later in the week while a sharp fall in the price of gold also
weakened the currency in the morning.
</P>
<P>
Bankers trust, believed to be a major buyer of Australian
dollars all week, helped push the Australian dollar up towards its
highs in the afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The revised wages data released Thursday had increased
speculation that the central bank would lower the official
interest rate from its present level of 5.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
A good barometer of where the market expects interest rates to
be in the coming months is the bill futures contract.
</P>
<P>
Traders said the Reserve Bank's quarterly report on the economy
to be released Tuesday will be closely read for clues on the
direction of interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar ended at 87.95 from 86.50 against the
Japanese yen and was at 1.3707 from 1.3700 against the German
mark.  
</P>
</TEXT>
