</P>
<P>
-- Scientists working on the DNA of a worm have found a gene
that might hold the secret of longer life. The gene, named daf-2,
regulates glucose metabolism in a tiny nematode called
Caenorhabdidtis elegans. But it also affects the worm's lifespan.
</P>
<P>
The Independent:
</P>
<P>
-- Private motorists could be banned from parts of Britain's
motorways including the M25 around London under radical proposals
being studied by ministers. 
</P>
