<DOCNO> XIE19970815.0135 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines' Domestic Investments Up in 1st 7 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Equity investments from local
investors soared by 371.3 percent during the January-July period
this year in the Philippines, the Board of Investments said today.
</P>
<P>
Data released by the board showed that inflow in domestic
investments reached 77.58 billion pesos (2.68 billion US dollars),
a dramatic increase from the 16.46 billion pesos (568 million
dollars) recorded in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The board approved equity investments with 100 percent local
participation grew by 208.37 percent to 26.96 billion pesos (930
million dollars) during the first seven months from 8.741 billion
pesos (301 million dollars) committed in the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
Joint equity investments also surged by 555.9 percent to 50.62
billion pesos (1.75 billion dollars) from 7.72 billion pesos (266
million dollars) last year, the data showed.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, foreign equity investments also showed an upward
trend amounting to 29.77 billion (1.03 billion dollars), a 135.84
percent increase from last year's 12.62 billion pesos (435 million
dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
