<HEADLINE> New Marriage Makes Mute Man Speak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Love the second time around has
put words into the mouth of a man who has not talked in the 21
years since his first wife divorced him, according to a report in
Beijing Evening News.
</P>
<P>
Shi Nengshou was so devastated by the break-up of his first
marriage in 1976 that he suddenly stopped talking. From then till
now, he has been mute, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The 45-year-old villager who lives in Doumen Village, Yuhuan
County of east China's Zhejiang Province, recently re-married.
</P>
<P>
During the wedding ceremony, the long-silent bridegroom got
drunk and cried, and uttered some broken sentences through his
happy tears. 
</P>
</TEXT>
