<HEADLINE> Australian Wool Market Steadies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The wool market steadied this
week despite a relatively high offering of 96,000 bales.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Council of Wool Exporters (ACWE) said today that
Wool International's eastern market indicator had firmed at seven
Australian cents (5.1 US cents) to close at 703 Australian cents
(523 US cents) a kilogram clean.
</P>
<P>
ACWE said a total of 95,978 bales were offered nationally.
</P>
<P>
The council said interest from European and Japanese sources
remained quiet, but purchases for China and India had provided a
good support, particularly for the Adelaide offering.
</P>
<P>
"It is felt that the current price level has found acceptance
and the firm market is expected to continue next week with a lower
quantity being offered."
</P>
<P>
Next week 79,445 bales are rostered for sale in Sydney and
Melbourne.  
</P>
