<HEADLINE> China Regulates Stock Exchanges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The State Council, China's
highest administrative body, has decided to place the country's
two stock exchanges under the direct administration of the China
Securities Regulatory Commission (CSRC), the nation's securities
watchdog.
</P>
<P>
The president and vice president of the Shanghai Stock Exchange
and Shenzhen Stock Exchange, will be appointed by the CSRC, which
will also nominate the chairman and vice chairmen of the
respective boards of directors.
</P>
<P>
"The State Council decision is of great significance to the
stability and standardized development of the Chinese securities
market, and will effectively safeguard the interests of
investors," according to the CSRC.
</P>
<P>
The CSRC appointed Tu Guangshao to replace Yang Xianghai as
president of the Shanghai Stock Exchange. 
</P>
</TEXT>
