<HEADLINE> 3 Killed in Cairo Shop Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Three people were killed and 273
injured when a fire ravaged a crowded shopping mall here Thursday
night, the Egyptian Al Ahram newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
Fire squads broke windows to help out late-night shoppers and
workers. The injured, most of them suffering from suffocation,
were rushed to hospital, according to an Interior Ministry source.
</P>
<P>
Red smoke billowing from the seven-story Al-Horreya Mall in the
plush Cairo suburb of Helioplis lit up the dark sky above, before
the blaze was contained in two hours.
</P>
<P>
The fire destroyed 25 boutiques and two cinemas which were
still operating and full of late-night customers who came to enjoy
a cool summer night.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary evidence shows that the blaze started in the fourth
floor as a result of electrical short circuit, according to the
source. 
</P>
</TEXT>
