<DOCNO> XIE19970815.0153 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Booming County-Level Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- China's county-level economy is
playing an increasingly important role in national economy and
currently accounts for more than 60 percent of the country's GDP.
</P>
<P>
County-level revenues also account for over 40 percent of total
local revenues, according to the Shanghai-based Business News.
</P>
<P>
The number of surplus rural laborers employed by township
businesses in counties is larger than the total work force in
China's state enterprise sector.
</P>
<P>
The county-level economy is not only responsible for
agricultural production, but also is the major source of
livelihood for a large segment of the population and the primary
producer of raw materials for the processing industry. Counties
have emerged as an important factor supporting rapid national
economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The urbanization and integration of urban and rural areas have
expanded along with changes in the rural economic
structure. Economists noted that county-level regions are expected
to be the first to make further breakthroughs in China's reform.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970815.0154 </DOCNO>
