<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liaoning Reinforces Basic Research </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province has spent 18 million yuan (2.2 million US dollars) over
the past six years to reinforce its basic science research
programs.
</P>
<P>
The province's natural science fund has grown from one million
yuan in 1991 to the present 7.5 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
In the 1990s, a total of 30 million yuan has been invested to
help establish 12 key provincial and central laboratories,
including those engaging in biological and metal-hydrogen research.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the province has placed emphasis on fostering young
and promising workers in the field of science. Every year,
one-third of the outlay from the provincial natural science fund
goes to finance the projects undertaken by researchers under age
35.
</P>
<P>
Over the past several years, about 500 young researchers have
received financial support from the fund. 
</P>
</TEXT>
