<HEADLINE> 900,000 University Graduates Find Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Most of the 900,000 students who
graduated from Chinese universities this summer have found jobs,
the State Education Commission announced today.
</P>
<P>
The commission said that some of them have been employed by
central government departments, and the majority have found jobs
in local provinces and regions or gone abroad for advanced study.
</P>
<P>
This year witnessed an extremely high number of college
graduates, which caused a glut in the employment market. But
thanks to efforts of various social sectors, the work of finding
jobs for the new graduates has gone smoothly, the commission said.
</P>
<P>
The students were upbeat about the job situation when they left
campuses, the commission reported. Even a few students who had not
yet been assigned appropriate jobs were calm about their
prospects, it added.
</P>
<P>
Many of the graduates have volunteered to work in remote
regions to do arduous jobs in response to the country's call,
according to the commission. 
</P>
