<HEADLINE> Over 20,000 Ugandan Refugees Return From Congo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Over 20,000 Ugandans fleeing to
the Democratic Republic of Congo have returned to their homes,
"The New Vision" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The refugees left their homes in Bundibugyo to escape attack
from the Allied Democratic Forces (ADF) rebels which invaded into
the District of Bundibugyo in mid-June.
</P>
<P>
Relief sources of Red Cross and World Vision at Uganda-Congo
border in Nyahuka told the paper that overwhelming majority of
the fleeing refugees have returned.
</P>
<P>
Many refugees crammed in make-shift camps in eastern Congo.
The majority of them are children, women and old people.
</P>
<P>
The ADF sent a team of some 50 rebels to Bundibugyo District
in the west to establish food sources in mid-June. But the
Ugandan army in the district foiled the attempt of the rebels.
</P>
</TEXT>
