<HEADLINE> Agassi Comes Back to Quaterfinal Level </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Andre Agassi of the United
States continued his comeback by winning a 7-5, 6-1 victory over
the third seed Alex Corretja of Spain to enter the quarterfinals
of the one million U.S. dollars RCA Championships in Indianapolis
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The 14th-seeded Agassi regained the form in Indianapolis tour
after his ranking slipped to 74 on the ATP Tour list. The three
consecutive victories he won here are his best performances since
reaching the semifinals last February in San Jose, California.
</P>
<P>
Spaniard Corretja, the world No. 5, became the highest-ranked
victim of the former world number one this year.
</P>
<P>
Corretja has to concede the upset together with other unlucky
seeds players as American world No. 1 Pete Sampras, Swedish No. 4
Thomas Enqvist and No. 6 Marcelo Rios of Chile as losers in the
third round.
</P>
<P>
So far, seven of the top eight seeds have been dispatched
except Carlos Maya of Spain, the fifth seed, who romped Australian
Richard Fromberg to a 6-2, 6-4 winning in 63 minutes. 
</P>
