<HEADLINE> Local Govt Elections Postponed in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's local government
elections have been postponed from next month to next year,
reported "The New Vision" daily today.
</P>
<P>
The postponement is due to financial constraints in the
country, Deputy Commissioner of the Electoral Commission, Flora
Nkurukenda was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
She made the remarks while presenting a paper on the
"relevance of local council elections and women participation" at
a workshop for civic educators and election monitors here
yesterday.
</P>
<P>
She said she cannot give a specific date for the elections but
hope the elections may take place within six months from August
18 this year, beginning with the process of updating the
register.
</P>
<P>
The local government elections were expected to take place
immediately after parliamentary elections which were held in June
last year but were delayed by financial and legal constraints,
said the report.
</P>
<P>
In November 1996, the Electoral Commission announced that the
local government elections would be held in March, 1997 and then
were put off to September this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
