<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Bans Sex Determination Test </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The Indian government today
banned doctors from determining the sex of the foetus and decided
to grant education scholarship to girl child born to a family
living below the poverty line.
</P>
<P>
In his address to the nation from the ramparts of the historic
red fort here on the golden jubilee of the country's independence,
Prime Minister Inder Kumar Gujral made this announcement saying
that the nation could not progress till women are granted equal
rights.
</P>
<P>
He said that women should be granted economic and political
rights.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister lamented the existence of child labor in the
country even after 50 years of independence and said that the
government would make efforts to send every child below 14 years
of age to school and sought cooperation from all in this regard.
</P>
<P>
In the man-dominated society of India, the status of women is
low. The announcement of the government to ban the sex test is one
of the steps to raise the status of women in the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
