<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Aids Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank has released 70
million U.S. Dollars to Zambia for balance of payment support,
local "Daily Mail" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Zambian newspaper quoted Finance Minister Ronald Penza as
saying here that the release of the money on Thursday followed
the successful Consultative Group meeting held in Paris last
month, when the Zambian government met the conditions attached to
the funds.
</P>
<P>
The Consultative Group indicated at the meeting that Zambia
will be given 435 million Dollars if there is sustained good
governance and strict adherence to the structural adjustment
program.
</P>
<P>
Of the money pledged at meeting 150 million Dollars is for
balance of payment support while the remainder is for project
support. 
</P>
</TEXT>
