<HEADLINE> Fujian Women's Federations Help Poor Women </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, August 15 (Xinhua)-- The women's federations in east
China's Fujian Province are endeavoring to help poor rural women
eliminate poverty and improve their lives.
</P>
<P>
Since 1995, the women's organizations in this coastal province
have put 6.66 million yuan in economic development of
poverty-stricken areas. They has also created opportunities for
about 54,000 poor women in these areas to work abroad.
</P>
<P>
According to an official of the Fujian Women's Federation, the
province currently has 271,000 people under the poverty line, half
of whom are women. To help them out of their circumstances, the
women's federations start by teaching the women farming skills
such as cultivating tea and fruit trees, feeding goats, hens and
rabbits, and producing mushrooms.
</P>
<P>
In the past two years, women's federations have held a total of
50,000 training classes for rural women, and great changes have
taken place as a result. The Women's Federation in Nanpin, located
in a mountainous region, has established 1,600 model
poverty-relief bases, including tea and mao bamboo bases. Together
they have helped more than 30,000 poor women get rid of poverty in
only two years.
</P>
<P>
And the Women's Federation of Xiamen Special Economic Zone
encouraged urban women to donate more than one million yuan to
help 1,100 poor rural women get jobs.
</P>
<P>
To support the aid-the-poor projects, the Fujian Provincial
Government will allocate an initial one million yuan to the Fujian
Provincial Women's Federation. Over the next year the sum will
increase to three million yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
