<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia to Curtail Illegal Entry from Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavia's Supreme Defense
Council is determined to strengthen security and supervision along
areas bordering Albania, the official Tanjug news agency said
today.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted a statement issued by the military press
office as saying that the number of Albanian people illegally
entering Yugoslavia has increased recently, and some of those
entering the country illegally may be involved in organized
terrorist activities.
</P>
<P>
The statement said some of those persons entering Yugoslavia
were supported by Albanian terrorists, while some Yugoslav
terrorist groups also join the Albanians and helped them cross the
border illegally. 
</P>
