<HEADLINE> Crimes on Decline in Ukraine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine registered a total of
345,000 criminal cases in the first seven months, down two percent
from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Interior Ministry statistics indicated that 73 percent of the
cases were solved during the period while the rate for last year's
corresponding period was 61 percent.
</P>
<P>
The police confiscated 2,677 illegal firearms and 15.6 tons of
drugs during the same period.
</P>
<P>
Economic crimes, especially in the financial sector, rose four
percent, of which 4,000 cases were solved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
