<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. to Increase the Number of Troops in Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The United States will start
rotating and soon increase the number of troops deployed in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
Troop rotation will begin on Friday, and the number of troops
will increase from 8,000 to 11,000 during the forthcoming Bosnian
elections, said a Pentagon spokesperson.
</P>
<P>
"It's an increase, a planned increase, and it's done for a
reason," Kenneth Bacon said today.
</P>
<P>
The in-and-out move, which will take place over a series of
weeks, allows for an overlap to occur just as Bosnia plans its
mid-September municipal elections, Bacon said.
</P>
<P>
Advance units of the Army's 2nd Armored Cavalry Regiment will
soon begin moving from a base in Hungary into Bosnia. They will
replace soldiers from the 1st Infantry brigade who will return to
their base in Germany, Bacon said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
