<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Domestic Light Industry Booming in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- According to statistics from the
China National Council of Light Industry, the total output value
of light industry topped 343.6 billion US dollars in 1996, 2.3
times up from 1992, according to today's "China Daily".
</P>
<P>
Output of some major products, including refrigerator, washing
machines, electric fans, irons, electric cookers and bicycles has
jumped to first place in the world, while that of beer, detergents
and salt stands in second place.
</P>
<P>
Along with the vigorous increase in output, the variety of
light industrial products also increase rapidly.
</P>
<P>
Every year, more than 10,000 new products appear on the
consumer market. The number of different light industrial products
now tops 260,000.
</P>
<P>
The light industry has not only satisfied the needs of the
domestic market, it has also become a major export-oriented
industry. More and more products exported have become technology
intensive.
</P>
<P>
According to a survey by the State Statistics Bureau of 40
consumer products in 1996, over 70 percent of the market for 33
products was dominated by domestic brand names.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, light industry has undergone comprehensive
restructuring. Some lalllllrge enterprises have broken through the
restrictions of industry sectors and regions and have established
economics of scale.
</P>
<P>
According to the third national industry survey, the number of
overseas-funded companies topped 2,000 by the end of 1995, making
up 12 percent of the total number of light industrial enterprises
and attracting about 14 billion US dollars from overseas, the
paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
