<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Firm Shifts Focus to China Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- A leading West European small
household appliance manufacturer has shifted its investment
priority to focus on developing the Asia-Pacific market, China
Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
Moulinex Group of France has announced in Beijing that the
company, having concentrated on the European market for half a
century, has now decided to shift its strategy and "spare no
effort to develop the Asia-Pacific market, especially China,"
sources in the Moulinex Beijing Representative Office said
yesterday.
</P>
<P>
China, with a population of 1.2 billion, is considered by
Moulinex as a huge potential market and, therefore, has been made
the focus of its Asia-Pacific development plan.
</P>
<P>
The company has made two major moves toward realizing this
strategy: establishing its Asia-Pacific headquarters in Hong Kong
and building up its largest Asia-Pacific manufacturing plant in
Zhongshan city, in Guangdong Province, sources in the Moulinex
Beijing Representative Office said.
</P>
<P>
Moulinex will use half of its total investment for the
Asia-Pacific region in China, promoting its products and
establishing the Moulinex (China) Co Ltd in Zhongshan.
</P>
<P>
A massive advertising and product promotion campaign will soon
be launched in China, sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Zhongshan manufacturing plant, whose actual investment
volume is not available at present, will first produce Moulinex
brand micro-wave ovens to be marketed in both China and other
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
