<DOCNO> XIE19970815.0194 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Investments Welcome in Bulgaria: Poll </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- One in two Bulgarians believes
that foreign investments can help the Bulgarian economy emerge
from the current crisis, according to the results of a recent poll.
</P>
<P>
The poll was conducted by the National Public Opinion Center in
July, in which 46.3 percent of the respondents were positive that
foreign investments would help the economy to recover.
</P>
<P>
While 24.1 percent of the respondents had the fear that the
national economy would become an appendage to foreign ones, 10.5
percent of the respondents held mixed views, with the remaining
19.1 percent having no opinion.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria will hold its first national forum on investment at
the end of October which is expected to attract more than 1,000
potential investors, investment agents, bankers, and managers of
leading European companies.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the parliament is reportedly considering enacting a
new law on foreign investment to remove barriers to foreign
investments, including the requirement for the minimum amount of
investment, the restrictions on the duration of investment in
securities, and the compulsory registration of foreign investments.
</P>
<P>
Credits, including capital leases and management contracts, are
recognized as particularly promising in attracting foreign
investments.
</P>
<P>
Land purchase by foreigners has been a concern to
Bulgarians. The ruling Union of Democratic Forces proposed to
remove the constitutional clause forbidding land purchase by
foreigners.
</P>
<P>
However, the poll of the National Public Opinion Center showed
that ordinary Bulgarians had reservations about the issue. Only
22.2 percent of the respondents favored selling land to foreigners
while 68.7 percent of them were against it.
</P>
<P>
In addition, half of the respondents opposed selling national
enterprises to foreigners and 37.7 percent of them favored such
moves. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
