<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Fireproof Material Production to Start in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, August 15 (Xinhua) -- A production base for brown
fused aluminum, with an annual production capacity of 60,000 tons,
will become operational by the end of this year in Taiyuan city in
China's Shanxi province.
</P>
<P>
Brown fused aluminum is a new type of fire-proof material that
is selling well on the world market and which has a wide range of
uses in buildings, metallurgy, the aerospace industry, and other
fields.
</P>
<P>
Many high-tech products now use the new material which is made
with a modern smelting furnace from Canada, using bauxite,
anthracite coal, and iron filings, all of which the province is
rich in. It also has a plentiful power supply.  
</P>
</TEXT>
