<HEADLINE> Zhuhai Becomes Model Environmental Protection City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Zhuhai, one of China's most
economically-developed coastal cities, has been selected as a
model environmentally protected city, today's "China Daily"
reported.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that the city has passed inspection by a group
sent by the National Environmental Protection Agency.
</P>
<P>
The title of "national model environmentally protected city" is
the highest honor awarded for outstanding urban environmental
conservation work.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Zhangjiagang in Jiangsu province was the first city
to win this title.
</P>
<P>
Zhuhai has conducted large scale activities in public
environmental education and comprehensive urban environment
improvement, the paper noted.
</P>
<P>
Many Chinese cities have attached importance to economic
development while ignoring environmental protection. The problem
has aroused government attention. 
</P>
</TEXT>
