<HEADLINE> Lebanese President to Visit Brazil in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Lebanese President Elias Hrawi
will make a six-day state visit to Brazil from September 1-6,
the Brazilian government announced today.
</P>
<P>
Invited by his Brazilian counterpart Fernando Henrique
Cardoso, the Lebanese president will visit major Brazilian cities
that will include Brasilia, Sao Paulo and Rio de Janeiro.
</P>
<P>
A delegation of five ministers, including Foreign Minister
Farez Boueiz, will accompany the president.
</P>
<P>
More than eight million inhabitants of Brazil have a Lebanese
background, and make up five percent of the country's total
population.
</P>
<P>
Senators and deputies with a Lebanese background account for 10
percent of the Brazilian Congress, while seven of the 26 state
governors in Brazil are of Lebanese origin.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian president will visit Lebanon in April, 1998.
</P>
