<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Net Sales of Industrial Sectors Up in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Led by food processing and
electronics sectors, overall net sales value of 21 surveyed
industrial sectors in the Philippines went up 11 percent in the
first five months of the year.
</P>
<P>
For the month of May, net sales value increased 8 percent over
the same month last year, according to the latest data released by
the Department of Trade and Industry Management Information
Survey.
</P>
<P>
Food processing topped the list of gainers, with net sales
value reaching 32 billion pesos (1.1 billion US dollars), a 4
percent increase from last year's 31.5 billion pesos (1.08 billion
dollars).
</P>
<P>
This is followed by electronics, with 29 billion pesos (1
billion dollars), while garments sector came in third, with net
sales soaring to 28 billion pesos (966 million dollars) from the
previous year's 22 billion pesos (759 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Other top gainers recorded in this period include cement,
non-consumer durables, construction materials and pharmaceuticals,
the data showed.
</P>
<P>
Sugar, on the other hand, was the top loser during the period
with sales dropping 53 percent to 392 million pesos (13.5 million
dollars), because of a decrease in demand due to stiff competition
in the domestic market with the influx of cheap imported sugar.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
