<HEADLINE> Sanchez Vicario, Pierce Humbled in du Maurier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- No. 6 Mary Pierce of France and
No. 11 Arantxa Sanchez Vicario of Spain failed to enter the
quarterfinals after Thursday's defeats at the du Maurier Open in
Torondo, Canada.
</P>
<P>
Pierce was ousted by Italy's Rita Grande 6-2, 6-2, and
five-seeded Sanchez Vicario, who reached the final last year, was
thrashed 6-4, 6-3 by her doubles partner 10th-seeded Mary Joe
Fernandez.
</P>
<P>
Pierce was clearly out of form by committing 24 unforced errors
and lost half of her services. She even gave up two playable balls
in the last set.
</P>
<P>
No. 69 Grande, who was more consistent and strong, had four
aces and three double-faults.
</P>
<P>
Trailed by 4-2 in the second set, Pierce called timeout and
went to the washroom. But Grande maintained her dominance to seal
the match in just over an hour.
</P>
<P>
Grande's quarterfinal rival will be top-seeded Monica Seles,
while Fernandez will face Magdalena Maleeva of Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
In other matches Thursday, seventh-seeded Conchita Martinez
overtook Indonesia's Yayuk Basuki 6-1, 6-4 and No. 3 Amanda
Coetzer edged No. 11 Kimberly Po 6-3, 6-3. 
