<HEADLINE> Plane Crashes in Indonesia, Injuring 11 People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- A commercial aircraft crashed
Thursday in Central Java, Indonesia, injuring all seven passengers
and four local villagers, Antara news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The plane crashed at 15:30 local time in the village of
Simongan in Central Java's provincial capital Semarang, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
Before the crash, the plane struck five houses and injured four
villagers who were just at home.
</P>
<P>
The injured victims including the pilot and co-pilot are being
treated in hospital.
</P>
<P>
A local villager said the plane seemed to be making some
abnormal moves before it nose-dived.
</P>
<P>
"We are still investigating the cause of the incident," a local
security official was quoted as saying.  
