<HEADLINE> Greece Skips University Games in Sicily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Greece has decided to skip the
upcoming World University Games slated on August 18-31 in Sicily,
the organizing committee said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In a telegram to the committee, Greece said it has decided not
to attend the Games "due to technical reasons", but failed to
elaborate the "reasons".
</P>
<P>
Nino Strano, head of the committee, depicted it "absurd" and
vowed to demand an explanation from the Greeks.
</P>
<P>
However, the withdrawal of Greece from the Games is considered
a tit-for-tat action against the criticism of Primo Nebiolo,
observers said.
</P>
<P>
During the World Athletics Championships in Athens, the Italian
who heads the International Amateur Athletic Federation, passed
the bucks to the organizers for the scarcity of audience and
claimed that Greece is in no way to solve its political and
economic problems through the hosting of the Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Currently, both Athens and Rome are among the top runners in
their bidding for the 2004 Olympic Games, and the International
Olympic Committee will cast their votes on September 5. 
</P>
