<HEADLINE> Van Basten Voted Best Player of 1990s </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Dutchman Marco Van Basten was voted
the world's best soccer player of the 1990s in a survey of Italian
coaches and former soccer stars, local reports said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Van Basten received 295 votes in the survey conducted by
Corriere dello Sport.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch forward, a three-time European player of the year,
led the Netherlands to the continental title in 1988 and retired
in 1993 after three operations on his right ankle.
</P>
<P>
He began his professional career in 1982 with Ajax Amsterdam,
and played seven years with AC Milan.
</P>
<P>
In the balloting, Argentine striker Gabriel Batistuta finished
second with 205 votes, and Liberian forward George Weah was third
with 198 votes. 
