<HEADLINE> Bosnian Muslim Party Opposes Religious-related State </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, August (Xinhua) -- The Ruling Muslim Democratic
Action Party (SDA) on Thursday said that the new Bosnian Currency
and flag should not carry religious symbols.
</P>
<P>
According to the Sarajevo news agency ONASA, SDA spokesman
Ismet Grbo said at a press conference Thursday that since the
country has four religions -- Islamic, Cathlic, Othodox and
Jewish, bearing of religious signs on the state symbols could
cause problems.
</P>
<P>
Last week, former U.S. envoy Richard Holbrooke won a concession
from the Serbs to drop their insistence on the printing an
Oxthodox church on the joint Bosnian currency, but an agreement on
the currency design has yet to be reached.
</P>
<P>
According to Grbo, the design of the flag is at its final stage
in the Office of the High Representative and there are two
proposals: one that the flag consists of green, red and blue
colors and the other that it has no colors, only a neutral symbol.
</P>
<P>
Grbo also claimed that there will be a rotation of Bosnian
ambassadors every two years among different nationalities,
although an agreement was reached last week by the Bosnian
presidency on dividing ambassadorships. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
