<HEADLINE> Bank of China Opens First Affiliate in Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The first affiliate of Bank of
China in Africa officially opened today in Zambian capital
Lusaka.
</P>
<P>
At the inauguration ceremony, Zambian Deputy Finance Minister
S. Simasiku said, it is the outstanding relations between Zambia
and China that has made it possible for Bank of China to set up
its affiliate in Zambia.
</P>
<P>
China has been "an all-weather friend of Zambia, it therefore
comes as no surprise that one of China's major banks is poised to
become a major player in our financial sector."
</P>
<P>
Bank of China, with its specialization in trade and finance,
will act as a facilitator for the further development in the
major sectors of Zambia's economy, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Bank of China is one of the world's highest-ranked banks in
terms of capital and assets and is therefore capable of making a
significant impact in the financial sector of this country," the
deputy minister said.
</P>
<P>
Zhao Ange, the bank's Managing Director and Executive Vice-
President, said at the ceremony that the Bank of China (Zambia)
will uphold its principle of providing best services for the
customers.
</P>
<P>
Zhao, who went all the way from China for the inauguration,
said the bank will abide by the local laws and regulations, make
great efforts to better serve Sino-Zambia and Sino-African trade
and financial cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The bank started its trial operation late last month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
