<HEADLINE> Six Police Officers Killed in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan police spokesman Peter
Kimanthi said today that six police officers and seven civilians
were killed during an armed attack on two police stations in
Mombasa, a southern port city, Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Kenya Television Network (KTN) today quoted a statement issued
by Jackson Kalweo, Minister of State in the Office of the
President, as saying that the government had launched speedy
investigations into the attack.
</P>
<P>
"Everything possible is being done to get to the root of the
attack. The government is determined to arrest those behind this
senseless act of violence," the minister said.
</P>
<P>
Kenyan Police Commissioner Duncan Wachira has flown to Mombasa
from the capital Nairobi to direct investigations into the attack
started by dozens of gangsters armed with machetes.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by Kenyan police in Mombasa said: "A major
security operation was immediately launched to net the culprits."
</P>
<P>
The police in Mombasa are holding four men suspected of being
among the seemingly well-organized attackers, police sources
said. 
</P>
